'''降F大調'''是基於F{{music|flat}}的小調，由F{{music|flat}}、G{{music|flat}}、A{{music|flat}}、B{{music|doubleflat}}、C{{music|flat}}、D{{music|flat}}、E{{music|flat}}組成。其調號除了六個降號外具一個重降號，屬於理論調。

== 簡介 ==
=== 音階 ===
降F大調的音階為：
:<score vorbis="1" lang="lilypond">  {
\override Score.TimeSignature #'stencil = ##f
\relative c' {
  \clef treble \key fes \major \time 7/4 fes4 ges aes beses ces des ees fes ees des ces beses aes ges fes2
} }
</score>

=== 應用 ===
降F大調常被標記為其[[異名同音|異名同音]]大調[[E大調|E大調]]，當中較著名的例子為[[路德維希·范·貝多芬|路德維希·范·貝多芬]]的《第三十一鋼琴奏鳴曲》。在第一樂章之呈示部中兩主題間的過渡段將[[降A大調|降A大調]]轉調到其[[屬音|屬音]]大調[[降E大調|降E大調]]；而在再現部中該過渡段則將第二主題以降A大調引出，該段即為以E大調標記的降F大調，作曲家大概認為E大調的調號更易閱讀。<ref>{{cite web|author=Donald Betts|date=2005|url=http://innig.net./music/betts-innervoice/|work=The Inner Voice|title=Beethoven’s Piano Sonata Opus 110|accessdate=2020-07-20|archive-date=2019-12-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191202213553/https://innig.net/music/betts-innervoice/|dead-url=no}}</ref>另外其《第四鋼琴奏鳴曲》末樂章及《[[第8钢琴奏鸣曲_(贝多芬)|第八鋼琴奏鳴曲]]》第二樂章皆有短暫轉到降F大調之處，皆以E大調標記。<ref>{{cite web|last=Gundersen|first=Finn S.|url=https://www.chandos.net/chanimages/Booklets/CH10960.pdf|title=Beethoven Piano Sonatas|year=2012|accessdate=2020-07-20|archive-date=2020-07-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200720074529/https://www.chandos.net/chanimages/Booklets/CH10960.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Davie|first=Cedric T.|title=Musical Structure and Design|publisher=Courier Dover Publications|year=2014|isbn=9780486172767|page=50}}</ref>

其他類似例子包括[[約瑟夫·海頓|約瑟夫·海頓]]的《第二十七鋼琴三重奏，Hob.XV:14》第二樂章；以及[[安東·布魯克納|安東·布魯克納]]在《[[第4號交響曲_(布魯克納)|第四交響曲]]》的[[尾聲|尾聲]]以[[終止式#正格半终止|弗里吉亞終止]]從降F大調回到主音大調。<ref>{{cite book|title=Elements of Sonata Theory: Norms, Types, and Deformations in the Late-Eighteenth-Century Sonata|url=https://archive.org/details/elementssonatath00hepo|author=James Arnold Hepokoski and Warren Darcy|pages=[https://archive.org/details/elementssonatath00hepo/page/n357 326]|date=2006|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=0-19-514640-9}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Bruckner's Symphonies: Analysis, Reception and Cultural Politics|url=https://archive.org/details/brucknerssymphon00hort|author=Julian Horton|pages=[https://archive.org/details/brucknerssymphon00hort/page/n138 127]|date=2004|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=0-521-82354-4}}</ref>[[理查·史特勞斯|理查·史特勞斯]]的《[[變形_(交響詩)|變形]]》也用到降F大調，評論形容此為對樂曲較早的E大調部分「以異名同音作苦澀的諷刺模仿」。<ref>{{cite book|title=Richard Strauss: New Perspectives on the Composer and His Work|author=Bryan Randolph Gilliam|pages=237|date=1998|publisher=Duke University Press|isbn=0-8223-2114-9}}</ref>此外[[塞繆爾·巴伯|塞繆爾·巴伯]]的《[[弦樂柔板|弦樂柔板]]》亦以此調作為高潮部分的解決。<ref>{{cite web|author=CRAIG STUART SAPP|date=2005-06|url=https://ccrma.stanford.edu/~craig/papers/05/p3d-sapp.pdf|title=Visual Hierarchical Key Analysis|accessdate=2020-07-20|archive-date=2016-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160818145808/https://ccrma.stanford.edu/~craig/papers/05/p3d-sapp.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

一個直接使用降F大調的例子為{{link-en|維克托·埃瓦爾德|Victor Ewald}}的《第四銅管五重奏》的第三樂章，其調號以B{{music|doubleflat}}在首、F{{music|flat}}在末（如右上圖片中的寫法）。<ref>{{cite web|title=Ewald, Victor Quintet No 4 in Ab, op 8|url=https://www.hickeys.com/music/brass/brass_ensembles/brass_quintets/products/sku035994-ewald-victor-quintet-no-4-in-ab-op-8.php|work=Hickey's Music Center|accessdate=2020-07-20|archive-date=2020-07-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200720074533/https://www.hickeys.com/music/brass/brass_ensembles/brass_quintets/products/sku035994-ewald-victor-quintet-no-4-in-ab-op-8.php|dead-url=no}}</ref>

